\f3\i\b The Inherent Buddha: Shingon\'92s Guide to Unconditional Self-Worth.
\f1\i0\b0 \
This pillar focuses on replacing conditional self-worth, rooted in performance and social image, with the radical, inherent value asserted by Shingon doctrine. The core objective is the realization of the innate luminous nature that needs only to be cultivated, not earned.\

